76 [140617223504576] INFO perfrun.launcher <> - the option was added --cpu-mask: Specify which CPU(s) <string> to collect data on. For example, specify "2-8,10,12-14" to sample only CPUs 2 through 8, 10, and 12 through 14.
76 [140617223504576] INFO perfrun.launcher <> - the option was added --event-mux-alg: Specify the event multiplexing algorithm. Possible values: sequence, timer, trigger.
76 [140617223504576] INFO perfrun.launcher <> - the option was added --event-mux-timeslice: Specify the event multiplexing time slice value as <integer>. The time slice specifies the duration between cycles for each event multiplexing group. The default value is 50 milliseconds. This option is valid only for timer-based event multiplexing. Specify the event multiplexing time slice value as <integer>. The time slice specifies the duration between cycles for each event multiplexing group. The default value is 1 millisecond. This option is valid only for timer-based event multiplexing.
76 [140617223504576] INFO perfrun.launcher <> - the option was added --event-mux-factor: Specify the event multiplexing factor as <integer>. It controls the switching of event multiplexing groups. The default factor is 50. This option is valid only for trigger-based event multiplexing. Specify the event multiplexing factor as <integer>. It controls the switching of event multiplexing groups. The default factor is 1. This option is valid only for trigger-based event multiplexing.
