77 [140617223504576] INFO perfrun.launcher <> - the option was added --aocl-source-file: Path to .source file. Find this in the compilation output directory of the FPGA application. Use this option to help attribute performance statistics to the source lines. If unspecified, AOCL profiler will attempt to locate the file in the current directory.
77 [140617223504576] INFO perfrun.launcher <> - the option was added --aocl-binary-aocx-file: Path to .aocx file (OpenCL flow) or host binary (DPC++ flow). If you do not provide this path: 1) For OpenCL flow, AOCL Profiler attempts to locate the file in the working directory. 2) For DPC++ flow, the collector assumes that host binary is used as an application to launch.
77 [140617223504576] INFO perfrun.launcher <> - the option was added --aocl-period: Specifies the number of cycles between readbacks from the device. The default value is 0 and indicates that the profiler should read back data as often as possible.
